commit.title: Add a test for double roundings when loading float_syntax module
commit.message:
Add a test for double roundings when loading float_syntax module

This prevents loading the float_syntax OCaml module, hence prevent
requiring Float on architectures (typically x86_32) where 80 bits
extended precision registers are used for floating-point values,
causing double rounding making floating-point arithmetic incorrect
with respect to its specification.

Well, this also prevents compilation on such architectures, maybe we'd
like to avoid that.
